  "text": "of posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD). In this regard, [CITATION_1] developed the PK Scale from the MMPI to assess PTSD in combat veterans. The PK Scale consists of 49 items from the MMPI that reliably discriminated between Vietnam veterans with and without PTSD based on a multimethod assessment including a structured diagnostic interview. Specifically, a cutoff score of 30 on the PK Scale correctly classified 82% of Vietnam veterans with PTSD [CITATION_2] .",
